uality of the research; • covers the research process from design, to collecting data, to dissemination and publication; • includes checklists and further reading, as well as useful examples and vignettes to illustrate how issues play out in practice. This book will be invaluable to researchers from a variety of backgrounds looking to increase participation in their research, whether postgraduate students, experienced academic researchers, practitioners or professionals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aPeople with disabilitiesxResearch. 0aSocial sciencesxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Research.2bisacsh1 aFearon, Kriss, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831111967560 cprintz978144735109240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447351115423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447351115/original  a978-3-11-119675-6  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles